Meanwhile, an even bigger story is unfolding in Los Angeles, Russell&rsquo;s old home. In recent weeks, it&rsquo;s become clear that the Lakers are willing to trade any and all of their young players to New Orleans for Anthony Davis. Endless speculation&mdash;and torment for the youngsters like Brandon Ingram and Kyle Kuzma&mdash;will culminate one way or another in just a few hours at the deadline&rsquo;s buzzer. Russell was once part of the Lakers&rsquo; young core; today, he seems fortunate not to be.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;I can&rsquo;t imagine what they&rsquo;re trying to block out,&rdquo; Russell says. Later, he adds: &ldquo;If [the Lakers] didn&rsquo;t let me go then, they were gonna let me go now, and I&rsquo;d be going through what they&rsquo;re going through. Best thing that happened in my career.&rdquo;

